    <h1>How PostPal works</h1>
    <h2>HOW TO REG&#xAD;IS&#xAD;TER</h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201219/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-19"><time>2020-12-19</time></a>
        - <span>SINGAPORE</span>
        - <span role="byline">Source: SINGPOST STRAITS TIMES GRAPH&#xAD;ICS</span>
    </section>

    <p>Step 1:</p>
    <p>Down­load the SingPost app into your mo­bile phone Step 2:</p>
    <p>Reg­is­ter by fill­ing up the re­quired in­for­ma­tion Step 3:</p>
    <p>Tap the PostPal icon on the home page of the SingPost app Step 4:</p>
    <p>Flat own­ers can ver­ify res­i­den­tial de­tails by tapping on the "Ver­ify with MyInfo" but­ton Step 5:</p>
    <p>Add users in the "Man­age Users" sec­tion un­der the "Ac­count" tab HOW TO COL­LECT MAIL Step 1:</p>
    <p>At the PostPal kiosk, tap the screen to be­gin mail col­lec­tion Step 2:</p>
    <p>Open the SingPost app on your mo­bile phone Step 3:</p>
    <p>Tap the PostPal icon in the app and a QR code will be dis­played Step 4:</p>
    <p>Point the QR code to­wards the scan­ner on the PostPal kiosk Step 5:</p>
    <p>Mail is dis­pensed for res­i­dents to col­lect</p>

